# Business Central API Conventions

- Keep API version and path construction explicit and centralized.
- Normalize base URL, company scope, and entity set handling before sending requests.
- Encode and validate OData query options (`$filter`, `$select`, `$top`, `$orderby`) safely.
- Prefer additive changes to request behavior; avoid silent breaking changes.

# Auth and Security

- Assume OAuth2 bearer tokens are sensitive; never expose raw tokens in logs/errors.
- Fail fast on missing tenant/environment/company identifiers with clear error messages.
- Distinguish auth failures (401/403) from query/resource errors (400/404).

# Response Handling

- Handle Business Central/OData pagination consistently when continuation links are present.
- Preserve raw API response data in `msg.payload` unless a transform is explicitly configured.
- Surface HTTP status and concise diagnostic context for troubleshooting.
